{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Benjamin was the father of Bela his firstborn, Ashbel the second son, Aharah the third,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Nohah the fourth and Rapha the fifth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Bela were: Addar, Gera, Abihud,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Abishua, Naaman, Ahoah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Gera, Shephuphan and Huram."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "These were the descendants of Ehud, who were heads of families of those living in Geba and were deported to Manahath:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Naaman, Ahijah, and Gera, who deported them and who was the father of Uzza and Ahihud."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Sons were born to Shaharaim in Moab after he had divorced his wives Hushim and Baara."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "By his wife Hodesh he had Jobab, Zibia, Mesha, Malkam,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jeuz, Sakia and Mirmah. These were his sons, heads of families."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 11,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "By Hushim he had Abitub and Elpaal."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Elpaal: Eber, Misham, Shemed (who built Ono and Lod with its surrounding villages),"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and Beriah and Shema, who were heads of families of those living in Aijalon and who drove out the inhabitants of Gath."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Ahio, Shashak, Jeremoth,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Zebadiah, Arad, Eder,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Michael, Ishpah and Joha were the sons of Beriah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Zebadiah, Meshullam, Hizki, Heber,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Ishmerai, Izliah and Jobab were the sons of Elpaal."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jakim, Zikri, Zabdi,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Elienai, Zillethai, Eliel,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Adaiah, Beraiah and Shimrath were the sons of Shimei."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Ishpan, Eber, Eliel,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Abdon, Zikri, Hanan,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Hananiah, Elam, Anthothijah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Iphdeiah and Penuel were the sons of Shashak."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 26,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Shamsherai, Shehariah, Athaliah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jaareshiah, Elijah and Zikri were the sons of Jeroham."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "All these were heads of families, chiefs as listed in their genealogy, and they lived in Jerusalem."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 29,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jeiel the father of Gibeon lived in Gibeon. His wife’s name was Maakah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 30,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and his firstborn son was Abdon, followed by Zur, Kish, Baal, Ner, Nadab,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 31,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Gedor, Ahio, Zeker"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 32,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and Mikloth, who was the father of Shimeah. They too lived near their relatives in Jerusalem."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 33,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Ner was the father of Kish, Kish the father of Saul, and Saul the father of Jonathan, Malki-Shua, Abinadab and Esh-Baal."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 34,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The son of Jonathan: Merib-Baal, who was the father of Micah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 35,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Micah: Pithon, Melek, Tarea and Ahaz."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 36,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Ahaz was the father of Jehoaddah, Jehoaddah was the father of Alemeth, Azmaveth and Zimri, and Zimri was the father of Moza."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 37,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Moza was the father of Binea; Raphah was his son, Eleasah his son and Azel his son."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 38,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Azel had six sons, and these were their names: Azrikam, Bokeru, Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah and Hanan. All these were the sons of Azel."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 39,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of his brother Eshek: Ulam his firstborn, Jeush the second son and Eliphelet the third."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 40,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Ulam were brave warriors who could handle the bow. They had many sons and grandsons—150 in all. All these were the descendants of Benjamin."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}